This section is authoritative. All visual implementation work must match the patterns below exactly. When in doubt, defer to the live CSS and component sources cited here.

### Chrome CSS

The document chrome CSS lives in `apps/web/src/index.css`. The current class is `diff-panel-conversation-shell` and must be renamed to `document-chrome-shell` as part of step 8. The explorer side panel variant gets `document-chrome-shell--explorer`. The visual properties are:

```css
/* apps/web/src/index.css */

.document-chrome-shell {
  background:
    radial-gradient(
      circle at top,
      color-mix(in srgb, var(--primary) 10%, transparent),
      transparent 38%
    ),
    linear-gradient(
      180deg,
      color-mix(in srgb, var(--background) 96%, var(--card)) 0%,
      color-mix(in srgb, var(--background) 92%, var(--card)) 100%
    );
  box-shadow: 0 32px 120px -72px color-mix(in srgb, var(--foreground) 40%, transparent);
}

/* Explorer variant: same gradient but denser — used when the explorer side panel
   is rendered alongside an expanded document view. */
.document-chrome-shell--explorer {
  background:
    radial-gradient(
      circle at top left,
      color-mix(in srgb, var(--primary) 7%, transparent),
      transparent 42%
    ),
    linear-gradient(
      180deg,
      color-mix(in srgb, var(--background) 97%, var(--card)) 0%,
      color-mix(in srgb, var(--background) 93%, var(--card)) 100%
    );
  box-shadow: 0 24px 80px -56px color-mix(in srgb, var(--foreground) 30%, transparent);
}

/* Any scrollable content viewport nested inside either chrome class gets a
   transparent background so the gradient shows through. */
.document-chrome-shell .document-viewport,
.document-chrome-shell--explorer .document-viewport {
  background: transparent;
}

/* Standalone viewport (outside chrome) keeps the existing card tint. */
.document-viewport {
  background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--background) 94%, var(--card));
}
```

The chrome class is applied to the **chat column div** in `ChatView.tsx`, not to the shell component itself. This lets it extend full-height behind the composer while the scrollable render body stays flex-constrained above it. See `ChatView.tsx` lines around the `diff-panel-conversation-shell` usage for the current wiring pattern to follow.

