### Git status visual treatment

Status treatment must stay below the threshold of an SCM panel. No red/green badge colors. Use the same `color-mix` softening pattern already used throughout the app:

```tsx
// apps/web/src/components/files-panel/ExplorerStatusPip.tsx

const STATUS_CLASSES = {
  modified: "bg-amber-400/40 dark:bg-amber-400/30",
  added: "bg-emerald-400/35 dark:bg-emerald-400/25",
  renamed: "bg-sky-400/35 dark:bg-sky-400/25",
  untracked: "bg-muted-foreground/25",
  conflicted: "bg-destructive/40",
} satisfies Record<GitFileStatus, string>;

export function ExplorerStatusPip(props: { status: GitFileStatus }) {
  return (
    <span
      aria-hidden="true"
      className={cn("ml-auto size-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full", STATUS_CLASSES[props.status])}
    />
  );
}
```

Directory rows aggregate child status at the highest priority (conflicted > modified > added > renamed > untracked). A directory with any changed descendant shows the aggregate pip; a clean directory shows nothing.

### Bottom fade overlay

Every document surface that scrolls must carry the bottom fade:

```tsx
<div className="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 h-16 bg-gradient-to-t from-background to-transparent" />
```

In expanded document main view use `h-24`. The `from-background` token resolves correctly against both the chrome gradient and the `bg-background` input bar because they share the same `--background` variable. Do not use `from-card` or any other token here.

## Assumptions and Defaults

- Explorer root is always `project.cwd`
- Worktree root is out of scope for this feature
- Header toggle is the primary entry control
- Selecting a file from the explorer enters expanded document mode immediately
- Collapsing expanded document mode returns to half panel preview, not explorer only
- Explorer and preview share the exclusive right side panel slot with diff and git
- Thread header and composer remain visible while document mode is active
- No dedicated explorer search box in this pass
- No ghost rows for deleted files in the explorer
- Clean tracked files remain neutral and only changed paths receive styling
- Distinct changed styling requires the small git status contract extension described above
